        "body": "## Overview\r\nThis PR represents a major refactor and pivot of the project to EventSphere , a lightning-fast, frontend-only event discovery platform. We transitioned from the previous full-stack Next.js architecture to a React + Vite setup to focus heavily on the client-side UI/UX and dynamic filtering capabilities.\r\n\r\n## Key Changes & Features Built\r\nFramework Migration:Fully migrated to React 19 + Vite for faster development and optimized client-side performance.\r\nPersonality-Driven Filtering Engine: Implemented a robust filtering sidebar allowing users to discover events based on Environment (Indoor/Outdoor), Crowd Size, Interest Area, and Personality traits (Introvert/Extrovert).\r\nInteractive Map View: Integrated `react-leaflet` for a dynamic, interactive map that plots events based on location, complete with user geolocation support and custom map markers.\r\nEvent Flashcards & Modal System: Added a sleek, popup modal (flashcard) system that opens when clicking an event to show full details seamlessly.\r\nSave for Later Functionality:Built a context-based bookmarking system allowing users to easily save events they are interested in.\r\nModern Navigation & UI: Implemented a new top navigation bar (Home, Explore Events, Map View) and polished the UI using Tailwind CSS and Framer Motion for premium glassmorphism and smooth animations.\r\nDocumentation Update: Completely rewrote the `README.md` to reflect the new architecture, tech stack, and our 3-person team's manual coding effort.\r\n\r\n## Note to Reviewers\r\nThis was a massive collaborative effort by our team of 3, built entirely from scratch without the use of AI tools. \r\n",
